{"id":3106,"date":"2014-03-26T09:27:02","date_gmt":"2014-03-26T14:27:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/new_logo_and_identity_for_society_for_general_microbiology_by_firedog.php"},"modified":"2014-03-26T09:27:02","modified_gmt":"2014-03-26T14:27:02","slug":"new_logo_and_identity_for_society_for_general_microbiology_by_firedog","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/new_logo_and_identity_for_society_for_general_microbiology_by_firedog.php","title":{"rendered":"New Logo and Identity for Society for General Microbiology by Firedog"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>(Est. 1945) &#8220;The <a href=\"http:\/\/www.sgm.ac.uk\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Society for General Microbiology<\/a> is a membership organisation for scientists who work in all areas of microbiology. It is the largest learned microbiological society in Europe with a worldwide membership based in universities, industry, hospitals, research institutes and schools. The Society publishes key academic journals in microbiology and virology, organises international scientific conferences and provides an international forum for communication among microbiologists and supports their professional development. The Society promotes the understanding of microbiology to a diverse range of stakeholders, including policy-makers, students, teachers, journalists and the wider public, through a comprehensive framework of communication activities and resources.&#8221;<\/p><!--more--><figure class=\"quarter\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/society_microbiology_logo_detail.png\" alt=\"New Logo and Identity for Society for General Microbiology by Firedog\" \/>\n<figcaption>Logo detail.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<figure class=\"quarter\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/society_microbiology_logo_colors.png\" alt=\"New Logo and Identity for Society for General Microbiology by Firedog\" \/>\n<figcaption>Color variations. Single-color version, not so good.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<figure class=\"quarter\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/society_microbiology_blobs.png\" alt=\"New Logo and Identity for Society for General Microbiology by Firedog\" \/>\n<figcaption>&#8220;The soft shapes are inspired by the brand mark and are the visual identifiers of microbiology.&#8221; Also acceptable: blobs.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<figure class=\"quarter\">\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/society_microbiology_application.png\" alt=\"New Logo and Identity for Society for General Microbiology by Firedog\" \/>\n<figcaption>Collateral.<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"(Est. 1945) &quot;The Society for General Microbiology is a membership organisation for scientists who work in all areas of microbiology. It is the largest learned microbiological society in Europe with a worldwide membership based in universities, industry, hospitals, research institutes&#8230;","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[9,72,25],"tags":[915,391,509,446],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3106"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments